Fifth Nasarawa State House of Assembly, (NSHA) will hold valedictory session on Thursday, June 6th 2019. This will mark the end of the fifth assembly in the state which was inaugurated on June 9th, 2015. Meanwhile, the 6th NSHA is set for inauguration on Monday, June 10th, 2019. According to the Clerk of the House, Mr. Ego Maikeffi Abashe, the development followed a proclamation letter sent to the assembly by the state Governor, Engineer Abdullahi Sule. Nasarawa assembly skips first 3 sittings after recess Plateau: 8th assembly passed 31 bills in 4 years Benue Assembly recalls 7 suspended members Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin